                    <h1>DropLaa API Reference</h1>
                    
                    <p>The DropLaa API allows you to integrate file sharing capabilities into your applications. All API requests are made over HTTPS and return JSON responses.</p>
                    
                    <h2 id="authentication">Authentication</h2>
                    <p>All API requests require authentication using an API key. Include your API key in the Authorization header:</p>
                    
                    <div class="code-block">
curl -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_KEY" \
     -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
     https://api.droplaa.com/v1/
                    </div>
                    
                    <p>You can generate API keys from your account dashboard. Keep your API keys secure and never expose them in client-side code.</p>
                    
                    <h2 id="upload">File Upload</h2>
                    
                    <h3>Upload Files</h3>
                    <div class="endpoint">
                        <span class="method-badge method-post">POST</span>
                        <code>/v1/upload</code>
                    </div>
                    
                    <p>Upload one or more files to DropLaa and receive a shareable link.</p>
                    
                    <h4>Parameters</h4>
                    <table class="param-table">
                        <thead>
                            <tr>
                                <th>Parameter</th>
                                <th>Type</th>
                                <th>Required</th>
                                <th>Description</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr>
                                <td>files</td>
                                <td>File[]</td>
                                <td class="required">Required</td>
                                <td>One or more files to upload</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>password</td>
                                <td>String</td>
                                <td class="optional">Optional</td>
                                <td>Password protection for the download</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>expires_in</td>
                                <td>Integer</td>
                                <td class="optional">Optional</td>
                                <td>Expiration time in seconds (default: 604800)</td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                    
                    <h4>Example Request</h4>
                    <div class="code-block">
curl -X POST "https://api.droplaa.com/v1/upload" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_KEY" \
  -H "Content-Type: multipart/form-data" \
  -F "files=@document.pdf" \
  -F "files=@image.jpg" \
  -F "password=secretpass123"
                    </div>
                    
                    <h4>Response</h4>
                    <div class="response-example">
                        <div class="response-header">200 OK</div>
                        <div class="response-body">
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "id": "abc123def456",
    "download_url": "https://droplaa.com/download/abc123def456",
    "expires_at": "2024-01-31T12:00:00Z",
    "files": [
      {
        "name": "document.pdf",
        "size": 1048576,
        "type": "application/pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "image.jpg",
        "size": 524288,
        "type": "image/jpeg"
      }
    ]
  }
}
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <h2 id="download">File Download</h2>
                    
                    <h3>Get Download Information</h3>
                    <div class="endpoint">
                        <span class="method-badge method-get">GET</span>
                        <code>/v1/download/{id}</code>
                    </div>
                    
                    <p>Retrieve information about a shared file without downloading it.</p>
                    
                    <h4>Example Request</h4>
                    <div class="code-block">
curl -X GET "https://api.droplaa.com/v1/download/abc123def456" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_KEY"
                    </div>
                    
                    <h4>Response</h4>
                    <div class="response-example">
                        <div class="response-header">200 OK</div>
                        <div class="response-body">
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "id": "abc123def456",
    "files": [
      {
        "name": "document.pdf",
        "size": 1048576,
        "type": "application/pdf"
      }
    ],
    "uploaded_at": "2024-01-24T12:00:00Z",
    "expires_at": "2024-01-31T12:00:00Z",
    "download_count": 5,
    "password_protected": true
  }
}
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <h2 id="management">File Management</h2>
                    
                    <h3>List Uploads</h3>
                    <div class="endpoint">
                        <span class="method-badge method-get">GET</span>
                        <code>/v1/uploads</code>
                    </div>
                    
                    <p>Retrieve a list of your uploaded files.</p>
                    
                    <h4>Query Parameters</h4>
                    <table class="param-table">
                        <thead>
                            <tr>
                                <th>Parameter</th>
                                <th>Type</th>
                                <th>Description</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr>
                                <td>page</td>
                                <td>Integer</td>
                                <td>Page number (default: 1)</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>limit</td>
                                <td>Integer</td>
                                <td>Items per page (default: 20, max: 100)</td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                    
                    <h3>Delete Upload</h3>
                    <div class="endpoint">
                        <span class="method-badge method-delete">DELETE</span>
                        <code>/v1/uploads/{id}</code>
                    </div>
                    
                    <p>Permanently delete an uploaded file and its share link.</p>
                    
                    <h2 id="analytics">Analytics</h2>
                    
                    <h3>Download Analytics</h3>
                    <div class="endpoint">
                        <span class="method-badge method-get">GET</span>
                        <code>/v1/analytics/downloads/{id}</code>
                    </div>
                    
                    <p>Get detailed download analytics for a specific upload.</p>
                    
                    <h4>Response</h4>
                    <div class="response-example">
                        <div class="response-header">200 OK</div>
                        <div class="response-body">
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "upload_id": "abc123def456",
    "total_downloads": 15,
    "unique_downloaders": 8,
    "download_history": [
      {
        "timestamp": "2024-01-24T14:30:00Z",
